node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JJ_MOBILEPHOTOGRAPHY in Russel Creek Park with @frozen_pixels. May be an image of lake, twilight, sky and nature.

node.text:
Hello everyone! It’s Dee again to share my final feature of the night with you!😊 🙋🏻‍♀️
.
.
“Do not go gentle into that good night.
Rage, rage against the dying of the light.” ~ Dylan Thomas 
*
*
Advice that the sun on this evening at Russel Creek Park in Plano, Texas that @frozen_pixels witnessed and captured seems to have heeded!! 🤩🌅💖💙 

If it wanted to end the day with a BIG beautiful blaze of glory, Texas-style, it succeeded, Right?! 🌞🎆 
.
.

I love how it divided the sky and waters below into magnificent hues of magenta pink and midnight blue, as it cast its last streams of light piercing through the inky blacks of the darkness to come.

And it put on one stunning show for those watching and waiting also. 😍👌 
Thanks @frozen_pixels for sharing the sight with us.
.
.
Please, JJMP Fam, take a moment to visit  the gorgeous gallery @frozen_pixels and spread lots of JJMP love and light while you’re there!!!! 😊💕💙
.
.
I look forward to seeing you next week!😃🙋🏻‍♀️ Dee (@iheart_alfresco_photos) 
.
.
Featured: @frozen_pixels 
Tag: #jj_mp_frozen_pixels
Location: Plano, Texas 
Device: Samsung Note 20 Ultra 5G

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JJ_MOBILEPHOTOGRAPHY in Góry Izerskie with @helpyourmemories. May be an image of one or more people, road, nature and tree.

node.text:
Hello and happy Sunday, JJMP fam!!🙋🏻‍♀️ 
It’s Dee here and I hope this finds you on a path full of fun opportunities today!! 🤗 💙🙏🏼 
.
.
“CHILDHOOD IS THAT STATE WHICH ENDS THE MOMENT A PUDDLE IS FIRST VIEWED AS AN OBSTACLE INSTEAD OF AN OPPORTUNITY”~ Michael k. Williams 
.
.
Perhaps because it’s been a weekend full of grey, rainy days where I am, this enchanting rain-soaked road captured so beautifully by @helpyourmemories jumped out and captured my heart this morning. 💙☔️

It also helped me retrieve a memory of a time when we took my teenage daughter and her friend to Disney World. A massive rain storm popped up that sent most of the crowds scrambling indoors. 
But not them. 
They took to the nearly empty Disney streets and began skipping in the rain and splashing through as many puddles as they could find. ☔️ It is still their favorite memory of the trip.🥰
.
.
I love the soft misty mood and tone of this shot, but what I love most is the way the light-drenched puddles are scattered about haphazardly on the path. I also love that the umbrella-toting adventurer is heading TOWARDS us and not away. 

So we can put ourselves in her shoes and decide…do we try to avoid the puddles….
Or jump in them?!?🤔

I’m pretty sure for me, I would try to avoid them…BUT I would make a game out of it…hop, skip, and jumping, and hopefully laughing my way through the nature-made obstacle course.😅

Maybe that is my best definition of “middle age.” 😜

What would your choice be?! 😃 Let us know in the comments below.
.
.
Thanks, @helpyourmemories for the memories! 😉
Please take some time to congratulate him and visit his beautiful gallery @helpyourmemories and spread lots of JJMP love and cheer while you’re there too!😘💙🤍
.
.
I’ll be back to share one more feature with you this evening!! 😃🙋🏻‍♀️ Dee @iheart_alfresco_photos
.
.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by JJ_MOBILEPHOTOGRAPHY on September 17, 2021 tagging @mementopdx. May be an image of cloud and text.

node.text:
Happy Friday and Challenge Announcement Day, JJMP fam!! 🥳🎉🙋🏻‍♀️ 
.
I’m on Cloud 9 that David @mementopdx is hosting his first JJMP weekend challenge for us!! 😃💙⛅️ 
Please give him a warm welcome and 
Then, read below for more insight into his creative mindset and imagination-inspiring theme.😃 💫 
.
.
.
“Hello mobile family! My name is David (@mementopdx), and I am thrilled that Dee (@iheart_alfresco_photos) and Jax (@jaxkm2) have asked me to be a guest moderator for this weekend’s challenge. I have been a photography enthusiast most of my life, but it is only recently that I discovered online communities that share that enthusiasm and genuinely encourage one another like @jj_mobilephotography and @raw_mobile_
.

Mobile photography reminds me of the catch phrase in the Pixar film, “Ratatouille”, “Anyone can cook” meaning that not everyone can be a great artist, but great art can come from anyone, from anywhere, and be about anything. My mobile camera is never far away, and I find that looking at the world through my always-at-the-ready camera lens changes how I see it. Details that I would have otherwise overlooked, often become the center point of an unfolding story.

I’m calling this weekend’s challenge theme “Look Again”. At first glance the meaning of a photograph may be obvious, but if you look at it again through the lens of your imagination you see something completely different. At first glance, the photo above is of a cloud break at dusk. But if you “look again” you might see warring Genie masters  rub their lamps as they prepare for battle, or maybe if you “look again” you can see steam trains of unsuspecting lovers just pass one another into the night.

Tell me what you see in your post. Use your imagination and have fun with it.” ~ David (@mementopdx) 
.
.
Theme: “Look Again” 
.
.
‼️Challenge Rules:‼️
▶️ MUST be following @jj_mobilephotography
▶️ Specify which mobile device you’re using.
.
.
Tag #jj_mobilephoto_325 👈
.
.
▶️New or old photos okay
.
▶️No previously featured (here on @jj_mobilephotography) photos please
.
#jj_mp_mementopdx 
Please pay our featured artist’s gallery a visit and show it some jjmp L❤️VE. Thanks!
